gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 104, Raptors 103
gameRecap.excerpt: Alex Caruso knocked down a corner three-pointer with 2.3 seconds remaining in overtime to lift the Bulls over the Raptors, 104-103. Caruso recorded 13 points, 13 rebounds, and two steals for the Bulls, while DeMar DeRozan (33 points, four rebounds, four steals) and Coby White (17 points, six rebounds, eight assists) added a combined 50 points in the victory. Scottie Barnes tallied 22 points, 10 rebounds, and 10 assists for the Raptors in the losing effort. His 2nd career triple-double, and 1st of the season. The Bulls improve to 1-1, while the Raptors fall to 1-1.
